                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">
                      <font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> A few nights ago in LDoN i was with a Sk that was having taunt problems, so since I was the slower he usually took aggro off of me and the other necro.  Now we weren't exactly trying to stay aggro free, infact we didn't care if we had aggro, but at a certain point I got a little low on mana so I decided to jsut slow for a few rounds before blasting again.  So i figure i will jsut turn pet taunt on, so I can jsut step away after a slow.  Well it worked.  Now this isn't bulletproof but I have been trying it more in groups and I have noticed a good difference in aggro.  I am sure there are other reasons as to why a tank may instantly hold better aggro but this is my theory.  Turning pet taunt on should considerably raise them on the aggro list, however because of coding they cannot out aggro a PC that is in the immediate range of the MoB.  But taunt should become more effective because the pets artifically raise the aggro list allowing the warrior to jump upwards from that.  Just a thought, but if your in a group with a weak tank try turning your pet taunt on and see if you notice a difference.</span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
