                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> my point was that when the pet taunts he raises the the aggro a warrior can taunt off of, or any class that uses taunt for that matter.  Pets get alotta aggro but are coded so they can't out taunt a PC that is in melee range.  So in effect pets act as a aggro buff for taunt classes especially for warriors that need it.  Pets raise the agro but CANNOT get aggro so the warrior then has a cushion to taunt off of.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
