                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Pressing taunt during an entire fight does nothing.  Trust me I've played a warrior on and off (now at level 65) for over 2 and a half years.  Here's a trick I do when in a pickup group as a warrior.  I pull a mob and attack it.  The shaman or enchanter would debuff it.  Usually this doesn't immediately make the mob run after them.  Then I wait for the slow message.  Soon as I see the enchanter or shaman cast their next spell I time my taunt button.  Usually the mob would begin to bolt right as the slow spell landed, but if I time it right the mob would turn back to me immediately.<br /><br />As I had said earlier there's more to agro than just that.  Things like pathing, whether a mob is snared/rooted or whatever has an effect.  About the mes spells.  I suspect that mes spells do their agroing right when it initially lands.  I could be wrong but I do know taunting before breaking does have its uses.  There's also the Area Taunt which is slightly different from normal taunt in ways other than it being AoE.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
