                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Pet taunt and warrior taunt work differently.  In my mind (I have been wrong before...), Warrior taunt is the standard Max agro+1 if successful.  Pet taunt, however, adds a fixed amount every time, which I am guessing scales with the pet level.<br /><br />A warrior taunting a mob that has a taunting pet attacking it generates more agro, because the taunting pet is generating a lot of agro on its own but the mobs are hard coded never to attack a pet when  PC is in range (Nerfed cause guilds were using a charmed pet to tank AoW way back). so the pet wih all the agro doesnt get hit but the warrior taunts and gets the pet's agro+1 which helps the war hold agro better.<br /><br />As necros are often agro kiters, we know how much agro a pet generates, with and without taunt, and can cast spells accordingly without breaking the limit and pulling agro.<br /><br />Usually.</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
